HEADWORD: Syllabism
<hw>Syl"la*bism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The expressing of
the sounds of a language by syllables, rather than by an alphabet or by
signs for words.</def> <rj><au>I. Taylor (The Alphabet).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

